From 01f14fabcfdc4cfba98b49f3cea645cbc8a5268c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hecheng Yu <kde-yyds@qq.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Feb 2026 21:30:04 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 04/43] base: Introduce Modded Pop-Up View

squashed:
1. base: Add Pop-Up View support
	Arman-ATI: Adapt for 16-qpr0
	kde-yyds: Adapt for 16-qpr2
2. Add PopUP dependencies from Sun-sdk
	Arman-ATI: Adapted classes
	kde-yyds: Fixup runtime crashes
3. Avoid InputChannel of Gesture Monitor being Disposed
	Due to 16-qpr2 changes, gesture monitor's InputChannel is disposed soon after initialization due to Pop-Up View changes, which breaks system gestures. As a workaround, this commit adds a setServerRetained() function to keep the gesture monitor.
4. Partially Refactor Pop-Up View
	In RisingOS Revived, the ported Pop-Up View is quite unstable. When dragging mini edge bar or pinned window overlay, there's race condition that randomly crashes system_server. Rather than finding the real cause of it, refactoring the mini window logic to avoid touching the unstable code is more simple.
	The original Pop-Up View implementation monitors the InputChannel itself, and relies on TaskPositioningController API to position window. Both behaviors have been deprecated since Android 16, so we should no longer use them.
	Without public InputChannel and TaskPositioningController, dragging on edge bar and pinned window overlay is broken. So we need to refactor the logic to use more standard move/resize methods.
	This commit introduced a fresh re-design of Pop-Up View:
	Overview
		A white pill-shaped bar is above the freeform window. Dragging around the bar can move the freeform window. Clicking the bar will show a menu for maximize/minimize. Dragging one of the 4 corners can resize (actually scale) the window.
	Changes
		DimmerWindow: It's no longer a dimmer window. Instead, it's an overlay with top white bar and 4 invisble resize handles. A small popup menu with window maximize and minimize controls is also implemented.
		DiimerWindow: Touch listeners are added for tracking window focus and for performing window move/resize.
		PopUpWindowController: We are using a short click effect for vibration, instead of traditional long wave effect.
		PopUpWindowController: Hide custom window control menu when touch events arrive.
		BackNavigationController: Send back navigation to fullscreen window below Pop-Up View when focus should be there.
		BLASTSyncEngine: Skip sync when Pop-Up View window is visible but not part of sync group, to avoid unwanted sync timeout.
5. Clean Up Unused Code for Pinned Pop-Up Window
	With our current re-design, we only use Mini Window Mode (102). Pinned Window Mode (101) is deprecated. This commit removes all code and resources for pinned window.
